## Field Definition ##
**Statistical & Analytical Plan** describes how study data will be analyzed and governed from a statistical perspective.

This MUST include:
- Definition of analysis populations or sets (ITT, mITT, PP, Safety, FAS)
- Primary and secondary efficacy statistical models (e.g., ANCOVA, MCP-Mod, mixed models, candidate models, hypothesis testing frameworks)
- Safety and exploratory endpoint methodology
- Handling of missing data and intercurrent events (e.g., multiple imputation, MAR assumptions)
- Multiplicity adjustment procedures (Bonferroni, Hochberg, alpha spending)
- Sample size determination and power calculations
- Interim analysis planning
- Statistical software used or timing of database lock (if described under statistical context)

